body:
In regressions of cases from the SystemVerilog LRM, legal case on 1800-2012 page 295 (or 1800-2023 page 347) errors out:

%Error: Internal Error: ../V3EmitCFunc.h:1735: Unknown node type reached emitter: EVENTCONTROL
 ... note: In instance 'sv12_lrm_p0295_class_intclass'
   |       forever @p.a begin
|               ^

**Code:**
```
class IntClass;
  int a;
endclass

IntClass address=new(), stack=new();

function automatic bit watch_for_zero( IntClass p );
  fork
    forever @p.a begin
      if ( p.a == 0 ) $display ("Unexpected zero");
    end
  join_none
  return ( p.a == 0 );
endfunction

function bit start_check();
  return ( watch_for_zero( address ) | watch_for_zero( stack ) );
endfunction

module t;
  initial if ( start_check() ) $display ("OK");
endmodule
```

**Version:**
5.044

**Environment:**
Centos 7.9，GCC 11.5

